<HR>
<H2> WIDE Project SCTP WG</H2>
<HR>
<BR> <BR> 
Description of Working Group:
<UL>
<LI> In this working group, we discuss topics related to SCTP(Stream Control 
     Transmission Protocol) which is receiving attention in the IETF community 
     as the successor of TCP.
     Discussions in this working group may also include topics related to other 
     transport protocols such as DCCP(Datagram Congestion Control Protocol) 
     or generic issues related to transport protocols as needs arise. 
</UL>
<HR>
<BR> <BR> <BR>
Our Software
<UL>
<LI> <A href=http://www.jp.nishida.org/dccp> 
       DCCP implementation on BSDs
     </A> <BR>Run on both NetBSD2 and FreeBSD5 
     <BR>
     <BR>
<LI> <A href=http://www.kozuka.jp/~kozuka/SCTP>
     Implementation of SCTP for FreeBSD5.3 
     </A>
     <BR>
     <BR>

<LI> <A href=http://www.csl.sony.co.jp/person/nishida/sctp_libnet.html> 
     SCTP support for libnet-1.1.2.1	
     </A>
     <BR>
     <BR>

<LI> <a href=http://www.jp.nishida.org/dccp/dccp.patch.20050920> 
    Patch to ethereal-0.10.11 for DCCP support</a> 
     <BR>
     <BR>

<LI> Patch to tcpdump for DCCP support <BR>
     This patch was merged. Get current tcpdump source code from <a href=http://www.tcpdump.org/daily/tcpdump-current.tar.gz> here </a>
     <BR>
<BR> <BR>
</UL>
